<p><strong>Removing a particular element/string from an array can be done in a one-liner:</strong></p>

<pre><code>theArray.splice(theArray.indexOf("stringToRemoveFromArray"), 1);
</code></pre>

<p>where:</p>

<p><em>theArray</em> : the array you want to remove something particular from</p>

<p><em>stringToRemoveFromArray</em> : the string you want removed and 1 is the amount of elements you want to remove.</p>

<p><em>NOTE</em> : If "stringToRemoveFromArray" is not located your in array, this will remove last element of array.</p>

<p>Its always good practice to check if the element exists in your array first, before removing it. </p>

<pre><code>if (theArray.indexOf("stringToRemoveFromArray") &gt;= 0){
   theArray.splice(theArray.indexOf("stringToRemoveFromArray"), 1);
}
</code></pre>

<hr>

<p>If you have access to newer Ecmascript versions on your client's computers (WARNING, may not work on older stations): </p>

<pre><code>var array=['1','2','3','4','5','6']
var newArray = array.filter((value)=&gt;value!='3');
</code></pre>

<p>Where '3' is the value you want removed from the array.
The array would then become : <code>['1','2','4','5','6']</code></p>
